sidebyside.p:
We substitute in the given equation.
4y^2 - (2)^2 \amp = 16 4y^2 \amp = 20 y^2 \amp = 5 y \amp = \pm \sqrt{5}
There are two points with x=2, namely \left(2, \sqrt{5}\right) and \left(2, -\sqrt{5}\right), as shown in the figure.

